[301755.17091, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1Baccepti\u001b[12Gg, not answering) costs\u001b[36Gthe full 1s curl\u001b[53Gcap\u001b[57Gonce\u001b[62Gper\u001b[66G5s\u001b[69Gwindow\u001b[76G—\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bvisible statusline stutter. Improvement: refresh the cache in a backgrounded\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bsubshell and alw\u001b[20Gy\u001b[22G render\u001b[30Gla\u001b[34G-known state.\u001b[48G\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mImprovements / semantics to capture for the baseline itself\r\u001b[2C\u001b[2B\u001b[22m7. \u001b[1mThe saved\u001b[16Gmetric is token-count,\u001b[39Gn\u001b[41Gt\u001b[43Gcost.\u001b[22m Cache reads counted\u001b[69Gat\u001b[72Gpar\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bunderstate\u001b[14Gthe\u001b[18Greal\u001b[23Gsaving\u001b[30G(~10×\u001b[36Gcheaper);\u001b[46Gcache\u001b[52Gcreates\u001b[60Gat\u001b[63Gpar\u001b[67Gunderstate\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btheir cost (1.25×). Since events carry \u001b[38;5;153mbaseline_cacheable_tokens\u001b[39m,\u001b[70G\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcost-weighted variant is computable from the same lines — \u001b[62Ghat's th\u001b[71G numb\u001b[77Gr\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B baseline study probably ac\u001b[34Gually wants.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B8. \u001b[1mClamping the total at 0 hides regressions.\u001b[22m For\u001b[53Ga study\u001b[61Gbr\u001b[64Gnch\u001b[68Gsp\u001b[71Gcifically,\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Ba neg\u001b[9Gtive day (proxy costing more than baseline,\u001b[53Ge.g.\u001b[58Glots\u001b[63Gof\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;153mpassthrough_reasons: not_profitable\u001b[39m traffic) is signal, not noise — \u001b[72Gonsider\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bre\u001b[6Gdering it red instead of supp\u001b[37Gssing\u001b[43Git.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B9. \u001b[1mThe counter is global, not per-session.\u001b[22m It \u001b[50Gums every client through th\u001b[78G\u001b[K\u001b[23;1H\u001b[20;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[301755.195366, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bsubshell and alw\u001b[20Gy\u001b[22G render\u001b[30Gla\u001b[34G-known state.\u001b[48G\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mImprovements / semantics to capture for the baseline itself\r\u001b[2C\u001b[2B\u001b[22m7. \u001b[1mThe saved\u001b[16Gmetric is token-count,\u001b[39Gn\u001b[41Gt\u001b[43Gcost.\u001b[22m Cache reads counted\u001b[69Gat\u001b[72Gpar\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bunderstate\u001b[14Gthe\u001b[18Greal\u001b[23Gsaving\u001b[30G(~10×\u001b[36Gcheaper);\u001b[46Gcache\u001b[52Gcreates\u001b[60Gat\u001b[63Gpar\u001b[67Gunderstate\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btheir cost (1.25×). Since events carry \u001b[38;5;153mbaseline_cacheable_tokens\u001b[39m,\u001b[70G\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcost-weighted variant is computable from the same lines — \u001b[62Ghat's th\u001b[71G numb\u001b[77Gr\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B baseline study probably ac\u001b[34Gually wants.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B8. \u001b[1mClamping the total at 0 hides regressions.\u001b[22m For\u001b[53Ga study\u001b[61Gbr\u001b[64Gnch\u001b[68Gsp\u001b[71Gcifically,\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Ba neg\u001b[9Gtive day (proxy costing more than baseline,\u001b[53Ge.g.\u001b[58Glots\u001b[63Gof\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;153mpassthrough_reasons: not_profitable\u001b[39m traffic) is signal, not noise — \u001b[72Gonsider\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bre\u001b[6Gdering it red instead of supp\u001b[37Gssing\u001b[43Git.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B9. \u001b[1mThe counter is global, not per-session.\u001b[22m It \u001b[50Gums every client through th\u001b[78G\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bproxy. Fine for a box-wide indicator, but don't\u001b[51Gread\u001b[56Git\u001b[59Gas\u001b[62G\"this\u001b[68Gsession\u001b[76Gsaved\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BX\"\u001b[6G— the live jump mid-test (772.8k → 908.2k fro\u001b[52G our own tur\u001b[65Gs) is the\u001b[75G\u001b[K\u001b[23;1H\u001b[20;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
