[301755.515156, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\u001b[3G\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mImprovements / semantics to capture for the baseline itself\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[22m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B7.\u001b[6G\u001b[1mThe saved metric is token-count, not cost.\u001b[49G\u001b[22mCache\u001b[55Greads\u001b[61Gcounted\u001b[69Gat\u001b[72Gpar\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bunderstate the real saving (~10× cheaper); cache creates at par understate\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthei\u001b[8G cost\u001b[14G(1.25×).\u001b[23GSince events\u001b[37Garry \u001b[38;5;153mbaseline_cacheable_tokens\u001b[39m, a\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcost-weighted variant is compu\u001b[34Gable from the same lines — that's the\u001b[72Gnumber\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe baselin\u001b[15G study probably ac\u001b[34Gua\u001b[37Gly wants.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B8. \u001b[1mClamping the total at 0 hides regressions.\u001b[49G\u001b[22mFor\u001b[53Ga\u001b[55Gstudy\u001b[61Gbranch\u001b[68Gspecifically,\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Ba negative day (proxy costing more than baseline,\u001b[53Ge.g. lots of\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;153mpassthrough_reasons: not_profitable\u001b[39m traffic) \u001b[49Gs signal, not\u001b[63Gnoise\u001b[69G—\u001b[71Gconsider\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Brendering it red instead of suppressing it.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B9. \u001b[1mThe counter is global, not per-session.\u001b[22m It\u001b[49Gsums\u001b[54Gevery\u001b[60Gclient\u001b[67Gthrough\u001b[75Gthe\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bproxy. Fine for a box-wide indicator, but don't read it as \"this session saved\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BX\" — the live jump mid-test (772.8k →\u001b[41G908.2k from our own turns)\u001b[68Gis the\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdemonstrat\u001b[14Gon.\u001b[K\u001b[23;1H\u001b[20;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
